.SH "NAME"
larcbk2rc - convert a scalar codebook that contains log area ratios to a  codebook containing reflection coefficients.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.B larcbk2rc
[
.BI \-x " debug_level"
]
.I "lar.scbk rc.scbk"
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
.I Larcbk2rc
takes an ESPS LAR SCBK file 
.I lar.scbk
and converts it to an ESPS RC SCBK file.
.PP
The input file 
.I lar.scbk
must be an ESPS SCBK file with \fIhd.scbk\->codebook_type = \fRLAR_{VCD 
or UNVCD}_CBK. 
Otherwise
.I larcbk2rc
exits with an error message.  
.I Larcbk2rc
creates and writes the ESPS RC SCBK output file 
.I rc.scbk.  
If "\-" is supplied in place of 
.I lar.scbk,
then standard input is used.  If "\-" is supplied in place of 
.I rc.scbk,
standard output is used.  
.PP
The header of 
.I lar.scbk
is included as a source in 
.I rc.scbk
and the 
.I larcbk2rc
command line is added as a comment.  
.I Larcbk2rc 
transforms the 
.I enc
and
.I dec
values in
.I lar.scbk
to reflection coefficients and stores them in 
.I rc.scbk.
The 
.I code
values 
and 
.IR final_pop []
values are copied from
.I lar.scbk
to 
.I rc.scbk.
The values of 
.I final_dist
and
.IR cdwd_dist []
are set to \-1 in
.I rc.scbk. 
(See SCBK (5\-ESPS).)
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
The following options are supported:
.TP
.BI \-x " debug_level"
If 
.I debug_level
is positive,
.I larcbk2rc
prints debugging messages and other information on the standard error
output.  The messages proliferate as the  
.I debug_level
increases.  If
.I debug_level
is 0, no messages are printed.  The default is 0.  
.SH "ESPS PARAMETERS"
.PP
The ESPS parameter file is not read by 
.I larcbk2rc.  
.SH ESPS COMMON
.PP
The ESPS Common file is not read by 
.I larcbk2rc.  
.SH ESPS HEADERS
.PP
.I Larcbk2rc 
reads the following values from the input SCBK file:
.RS 5
\fI
.nf
common.type
common.ndrec
\fP
.RE
.fi
The following items are copied from the header of 
.I lar.scbk\fR 
to the header of 
.I rc.scbk:
.RS 5
.nf
\fI
variable.comment
hd.scbk\->num_cdwds
hd.scbk\->element_num
\fP
.RE
.fi
The following values are set in the header of
.I rc.scbk:
.RS 5
.nf
\fIhd.scbk\->num_items\fP = 0
\fIhd.scbk\->distortion\fP = \-1
\fIhd.scbk\->convergence\fP = \-1
\fIhd.scbk\->codebook_type\fP = RC_CBK, RC_UNVCD_CBK or RC_VCD_CBK
depending on if \fIcodebook_type\fR of the input file is LAR_CBK,
LAR_UNVCD_CBK, or LAR_VCD_CBK.
